    <!-- UX3: In-app help -->
    <string name="help_title">Usage Guide</string>
    <string name="help_intro">ProRF calculates RF link budgets — accounting for all gains and losses from transmitter to receiver — giving you margin, SNR, EIRP, and sensitivity in real time.</string>
    <string name="help_nodes_title">Node Types</string>
    <string name="help_nodes_body">TX  Signal source, amplifiers, TX antenna. Add power and gain to the chain.\n\nLOSS  Cables, filters, attenuators. Reduce signal power.\n\nPROP  Free-space loss, rain fading, atmospheric absorption. Calculated from global frequency and distance.\n\nRX  RX antenna, LNA, mixer, receiver. Friis cascade determines the system noise figure.</string>
    <string name="help_metrics_title">Key Metrics</string>
    <string name="help_metrics_body">EIRP  Power at the last TX node (dBm).\n\nSNR  Signal above the noise floor at the receiver (dB).\n\nMargin  SNR minus receiver sensitivity. Positive = link closes.\n\nSensitivity  Minimum detectable signal, set by bandwidth, noise figure, and temperature.</string>
    <string name="help_tips_title">Tips</string>
    <string name="help_tips_body">Arrange nodes top-to-bottom: TX chain → propagation → RX chain.\n\nGlobal Frequency and Distance control the free-space path loss.\n\nGray \"Reference\" parameters are saved for notes but don\'t affect this calculation.\n\nTap \"Details →\" in the results bar to open full analysis.</string>

